Need SMALLER representation for complicated problems.
Generally phi is the simplified/smaller representation
The tradeoff is to capture the full character of the state while minimizing size of the representation

update theta with TD error (using learning rate alpha and gradient theta)
Minimizes squared error

Uses Q function that can be parameterized by theta i

Estimator is biased
Double use of estimator introduces a bias
Use two sets of parameters, one for Q value, one for argmax
Use samples with high loss (i.e. select samples most useful for learning)
Instead of uniform sampling distribution, use probability distribution scaled from weighted temporal difference error
select optimizer, e.g. ADAM
Sample efficiency in real-world is a big consideration
